Source.Title: The HITRAN 2008 molecular spectroscopic database
Source.SourceName: Journal of Quantitative Spectroscopy and Radiative Transfer

Function.Comments: This function gives the pressure- and temperature-dependence of the Lorentzian component of the pressure-broadened line width (HWHM)

Argument.Name: p
Argument.Description: The partial pressure of the broadening species, in atm

Parameter.Name: gammaL_ref
Parameter.Description: The Lorentzian HWHM of the line, broadened at Tref = 296 K and broadening species partial pressure pref = 1atm

Parameter.Name: n
Parameter.Description: The temperature exponent of the gammaL function

Function.Comments: This function gives the pressure-dependence of the absorption line wavenumber shift: nu = nu_ref + (delta).(p/pref)

Argument.Name: p
Argument.Description: The pressure of the shifting environment, in atm

Parameter.Name: delta_ref
Parameter.Description: The pressure-shift of the absorption line at pref = 1 atm

Lineshape.Name: Lorentzian
Lineshape.Comments: The temperature-dependent pressure broadening Lorentzian lineshape
